Cop Land is a 1997 American crime drama film written and directed by James Mangold. It features an ensemble cast including Sylvester Stallone, Harvey Keitel, Robert De Niro, Ray Liotta, Janeane Garofalo, Michael Rapaport, Robert Patrick, Peter Berg, Annabella Sciorra, Cathy Moriarty, Arthur Nascarella, and John Spencer.The story follows a sheriff in a small New Jersey town dominated by corrupt New York City cops. Their corruption grows until he can no longer allow himself to stand by and do nothing.Critics gave the film generally positive reviews and it has a 73% "fresh" rating at RottenTomatoes.com, based on 62 reviews.
